The paper proposes a new embedding model for knowledge graph completion and search personalization, which involves natural language processing, machine learning, and database systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) due to the use of natural language processing techniques. Finally, cs.DB (Database) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with knowledge graph completion, which is a task related to database systems.
